div.p: The official URL for this implementation guide is:
FHIR Implementation Guide for Care - a Digital Public Good enabling Decentralized Administration of Healthcare. This IG documents all Care EMR models as FHIR R5 resources, profiles, and extensions.

description.value: Foundational administrative resources: Patient, Related Person, User, User Roles, Permissions, Consent, Facility, Department, Location, Care Team, Device
Definitional resources: Questionnaire, Observation Definition, Specimen Definition, Device Definition, ValueSet, Code System, Plan Definition, Activity Definition

Clinical resources: Encounters, Allergy Intolerance, Immunization, Risk Assessment, Procedure, Questionnaire Response, Observation, Condition, Care Plan, Goal, DocumentReference, Medication Request, Medication Statement, Medication Administration, Task, Threads, Messages
Scheduling resources: Schedule, Token Slot, Token Booking, Availability, Availability Exception
Pharmacy and inventory resources: Medication Dispense, Inventory Item, InventoryReport, Transport, Device Dispense, Supply Request, SupplyDelivery
Laboratory and diagnostic resources: Service Request, Specimen, Media, Diagnostic Report, Imaging Study
Financial resources: Charge Item, Charge Item Definition, Invoice, Account, Payment Notice, Payment Reconciliation, Claim, ClaimResponse, Coverage, Explanation Of Benefit
Care-specific extensions
Value sets and code systems
The following artifacts define the types of individuals and/or systems that will interact as part of the use cases covered by this implementation guide.
The following artifacts describe the specific requirements to be met by systems compliant with the implementation guide.

The following artifacts define the specific capabilities that different types of systems are expected to have in order to comply with this implementation guide. Systems conforming to this implementation guide are expected to declare conformance to one or more of the following capability statements.
These are custom operations that can be supported by and/or invoked by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define the types of messages that can be sent and/or received by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define the properties by which a RESTful server can be searched. They can also be used for sorting and including related resources.
These define activities that can be performed as part of content in this implementation guide.
These define workflows, rules, strategies, or protocols as part of content in this implementation guide.
These define measures as part of content in this implementation guide.
These define logic, asset collections and other libraries as part of content in this implementation guide.
These define collections of interrelated resources that are useful to pass around as a group.
These define data models that represent the domain covered by this implementation guide in more business-friendly terms than the underlying FHIR resources.
These define forms used by systems conforming to this implementation guide to capture or expose data to end users.

These are profiles on resources or data types that describe patterns used by other profiles, but cannot be instantiated directly. I.e. instances can conform to profiles *based* on these abstract profiles but do not declare conformance to the abstract profiles themselves.
These define constraints on FHIR resources for systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define sets of codes used by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define new code systems used by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define identifier and/or code system identities used by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define transformations to convert between data structures used by systems conforming to this implementation guide.
These define transformations to convert between codes by systems conforming with this implementation guide.
These test plans are available to verify test coverage for this implementation guide
These test definitions are available to FHIR test engines to verify systems are conforming to this implementation guide
These define groups of interrelated examples that demonstrate one or more of the workflows supported by this implementation guide.
These are example instances that show what data produced and consumed by systems conforming with this implementation guide might look like.
These are example instances that are not governed by this implementation guide, but which are necessary to support other examples defined in the IG.
These are resources that are used within this implementation guide that do not fit into one of the other categories.
A healthcare facility in the Care network
Capability statement for the Care FHIR server, describing the supported resources, operations, and search parameters.
Profile for Account resource representing patient accounts and billing information in the Care system.
Profile for ActivityDefinition resource representing activity definitions and service catalog items in the Care system.
Profile for AllergyIntolerance resource representing patient allergies and intolerances in the Care system.
Profile for ChargeItemDefinition resource representing charge item definitions and pricing in the Care system.
Profile for ChargeItem resource representing chargeable items in the Care system.
Profile for Condition resource representing patient conditions, diagnoses, and health problems in the Care system.
Profile for Consent resource representing patient consents in the Care system.
Patient's current home address as plain text.
Profile for Device resource representing medical devices and equipment in the Care system.
Profile for DiagnosticReport resource representing diagnostic test results and reports in the Care system.
Profile for Encounter resource representing patient visits and interactions in the Care system.
Profile for Organization resource representing facility-scoped organizations in the Care system.
Extension to indicate facility scoping for resources that can be scoped to a specific facility.
Profile for HealthcareService resource representing healthcare services offered in the Care system.
Profile for Invoice resource representing billing invoices in the Care system.
Profile for Location resource representing facility locations, beds, rooms, and other physical spaces in the Care system.
Profile for MedicationAdministration resource representing medication administration events in the Care system.
Profile for MedicationDispense resource representing medication dispensing events in the Care system.
Profile for MedicationRequest resource representing medication prescriptions and requests in the Care system.
Profile for MedicationStatement resource representing patient medication usage statements in the Care system.
Profile for ObservationDefinition resource representing observation definitions and lab test catalog items in the Care system.
Profile for Observation resource representing clinical observations, measurements, and assessments in the Care system.
Extension to capture organization hierarchy relationships including parent, root organization, and level cache for efficient querying.
Profile for Organization resource representing organizational structures in the Care system, including hierarchical relationships.
A profile that accurately represents patient demographic and contact details as specified in the Care EMR system.
Profile for PaymentReconciliation resource representing payment reconciliations in the Care system.
Patient's permanent billing address as plain text.
A simple extension to hold patient's phone numbers, including primary and emergency, as plain strings.
Profile for Questionnaire resource representing forms and questionnaires in the Care system.
Profile for Schedule resource representing appointment schedules in the Care system.
Profile for ServiceRequest resource representing service requests and orders in the Care system.
Profile for SpecimenDefinition resource representing specimen definitions and requirements in the Care system.
Profile for Specimen resource representing biological specimens in the Care system.
Profile for SupplyDelivery resource representing supply deliveries in the Care system.
Profile for SupplyRequest resource representing supply requests in the Care system.
Extension to capture tags and metadata for resources. Tags are used for categorization and filtering.
Value set for condition clinical and verification statuses used in the Care system.
Value set for encounter statuses used in the Care system.
Value set for location statuses used in the Care system.
Value set for medication request and statement statuses used in the Care system.
Value set for observation statuses used in the Care system.
Value set for organization types used in the Care system.
